<font color="#FF0000">JUST WANTING TO SHARE</font><br>
<tt>Sun Feb 15  2:39:31 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
I so appreciate all the dialog I have read from this site, so often wanting to express everything but not wanting to be inappropriate. For me response is something to be pondered first, nothing to jump right into ... many times, a reaction is pure emotion and lacks thought. *big smile* And you have all given me much to think about.<br><br>
I'd like to share something that I wrote. It is for all to read and assess in their own way ... yet I was moved to share it after reading several posts by Arthur on another thread.<br><br>
Ever so slowly<br>
   clouds gently sweep across an untamed sky<br>
A blue facade of calm suddenly slips away<br>
   taking with it the warm embrace of security<br>
Darkened skies emerge ...<br>
   a cold chill sweeps the mountains below<br>
The serenity of the mountains is soon covered <br>
   by a blanket of uncertainty.<br>
Creatures large and small seek shelter<br>
   as the storm draws near<br><br>
There is one ...<br><br>
One who embraces the thundering skies ...<br>
One who chases the chill of uncertainty ...<br>
One whose very spirit is rejuvinated ...<br><br>
Brother Eagle   ...   I call to you<br><br>
You for whom I have so much respect<br>
You are the balance between uncertainty and security ...<br>
for in uncertainty you have found security<br>
It is the driving force of your very spirit ...<br>
It is the window to your soul<br><br>

